# Mafqood App - Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env and update with your values

# ===== Backend API Configuration =====

# API Base URL for backend services
# For local development:
# - iOS Simulator: http://localhost:8000
# - Android Emulator: http://10.0.2.2:8000  
# - Physical Device: http://YOUR_LOCAL_IP:8000 (e.g., http://192.168.1.100:8000)
# For production: https://your-production-api.com
EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://localhost:8000

# ===== Optional Configuration =====

# API Timeout (milliseconds) - Default: 30000 (30 seconds)
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_TIMEOUT=30000

# ===== Setup Instructions =====

# 1. Physical Device Testing:
#    - Find your local IP: ipconfig (Windows) or ifconfig (Mac/Linux)
#    - Update EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL with your IP address
#    - Ensure backend is running and accessible on your network
#    - Both device and computer must be on same WiFi network

# 2. Backend Requirements:
#    - FastAPI backend must be running on specified URL
#    - Backend should handle CORS for mobile requests
#    - All API endpoints must match routes defined in src/api/config.ts

# 3. Production Deployment:
#    - Update EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL to production backend URL
#    - Use HTTPS for secure communication
#    - Ensure backend can handle mobile traffic

# 4. Environment Variable Usage:
#    - EXPO_PUBLIC_* variables are embedded at build time
#    - Changes require app restart (Stop expo and start again)
#    - Never commit .env file to version control
